<p>Im wondering if the image in the web ui is trying to say ‘remove the jumper’, not ‘put it here’. I think that was my main source of confusion.</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":6,"updated_at":"2024-10-09T11:08:31.275Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":37,"readers_count":36,"score":12.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":472609,"topic_slug":"romi-digital-i-o-issues","display_username":"Ryan Yohnk","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":27102,"username":"zeequeue","name":"zeequeue","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/zeequeue/{size}/11778_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":45842,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/romi-digital-i-o-issues/472609/3","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3432742,"name":"zeequeue","username":"zeequeue","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/zeequeue/{size}/11778_2.png","created_at":"2024-10-09T11:40:36.291Z","cooked":"<p>Ah so the jumper is there to provide power to that middle row (which for servos, is the 5V line). In Digital In mode, the pins are set to use a pull up resistor, so you should be able to connect signal → ground to get a response</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":6,"updated_at":"2024-10-09T11:40:36.291Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_l